KANO – Chairman, House Committee on Appropriations, Senator Barau Jibrin on Saturday evening clinched the All Progressives Congress senatorial ticket for Kano North. No fewer than 697 delegates drawn from 16 local governments had assembled at the Party zonal office, Bichi to affirm the ranking Senator for a third attempt to the Red chamber. Senator Jibrin’s political feat was made possible by the Kano state governor, Dr. Abdullahi Umar Ganduje who voluntarily stepped down his ambition. -Advertisement- However, delegates were however voted to affirm Senator Jibrin’s candidacy under the full watch of INEC officials, party officials, observers and security agents. In his post-electoral victory speech, Senator Barau Jibrin commended the state governor, Dr. Abdullahi Umar Ganduje for his sacrifice and uniting role in uniting the party. Jibrin said his reelection to contest the Senate was a testimony that Kano APC was one strong family. Jibrin assured that he would continue to carry along everyone from the area regardless of his party affiliation.